&reftitle.setup;
&reftitle.required;
pht requires a ZTS (Zend Thread Safety) version of PHP. Currently, only PHP 7.2 is supported. Support for PHP 7.3 (which will be released at the end of 2018) will be coming soon. PHP 7.0 and 7.1 are unsafe to support, due to race conditions in ZTS mode.
pht should be compatible for any OS with the pthread library (or pthread-win32 library, which is for Windows).
&reftitle.install;
pht releases are hosted (along with its source code) on the pht GitHub repository. Unix developers will need to build from source (instructions here). Windows developers can download the appropriate .dll file from the repository's releases page. They will need to ensure that the provided pthreadVC2.dll file (which is distributed alongside the extension's .dll file) is made available in their PATH environment variable.
&reftitle.runtime; &no.config;
